Package com.uddernetworks.emojide.gui.text

Interface TextBlock

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultTextBlock, DynamicTextBlock
    public interface TextBlock
    A statically-sized block of text that is meant for the dynamic content of a component containing text. This contains methods to add, remove, and move characters as if they were being changed with a keyboard.

      • getCharArray

        default char[][] getCharArray()
        Gets the characters of the TextBlock. The 2D array is just an array of rows, meaning the first length is the height, and the inner length is the width.
        Returns:
        A 2D array of characters.

        Returns:
        A grid of characters

        void addChar​(char character,
             int x,
             int y)

        x - The X position of the grid
